## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Friction Strategy:** This "Ultimate" flow adds several steps (Verification, Demographic Selection, Quality Checks). In the "Looksmaxxing" niche, this friction builds **authority**—the user feels they are getting a medical-grade report. Are you comfortable with this shift toward a longer, more detailed flow?

> [!CAUTION]
> **Data Privacy:** Phase 4 (Demographic Adjustments) requires collecting Age/Ethnicity. We will ensure this is handled purely for "Metric Normalization" and not stored in a sensitive way.

## Open Questions
1. **Manual Verification:** Should it be *mandatory* for the first scan, or always optional?
2. **Interpretability:** Do you want the "Explain My Score" data to be simplified for casual users, or stay purely technical for "Scientific Authority"?
